### 1. Constraint Validation Kya Hai?
HTML5 mein browsers automatically input check karte hain rules ke against (jaise email format, required field, number range).  
Isse fast feedback milta hai aur kam JavaScript likhna padta hai.

### HTML5 Built-in Validation Attributes

| Attribute              | Asan Description                                      | Example |
|------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------|---------|
| `required`             | Field khali nahi chhod sakte                           | `<input required>` |
| `minlength` / `maxlength` | Text ki length limit                                | `<input minlength="6" maxlength="12">` |
| `min` / `max`          | Number, date, range ke liye minimum/maximum value     | `<input type="number" min="1" max="100">` |
| `step`                 | Number mein increment (0.5, 10 etc.)                  | `<input type="number" step="5">` |
| `type`                 | Email, url, tel, number, date etc. automatic check    | `<input type="email">` |
| `pattern`              | Custom regex (regular expression)                     | `<input pattern="^[0-9]{5}$" title="5 digit zip code">` |

### CSS Pseudo-classes for Visual Feedback

| Pseudo-class             | Kab Apply Hota Hai?                              | Common Use |
|--------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|------------|
| `:valid`                 | Input sahi hai                                   | Green border |
| `:invalid`               | Input galat hai                                  | Red border |
| `:required`              | Required field                                   | Highlight |
| `:optional`              | Optional field                                   | Light style |
| `:user-valid` / `:user-invalid` | User ne kuch enter kiya aur ab valid/invalid hai | Better UX (sirf user interaction ke baad) |

**Example:**
```css
input:invalid {
  border: 2px solid red;
}
input:valid {
  border: 2px solid green;
}
```

### JavaScript Constraint Validation API

**Key Properties (on form element or input)**

| Property / Object         | Kya Batata Hai? |
|---------------------------|-----------------|
| `form.checkValidity()`    | Poora form valid hai ya nahi (true/false) |
| `input.validity`          | Detailed object (`valueMissing`, `typeMismatch`, `tooShort`, `patternMismatch` etc.) |
| `input.validationMessage` | Browser ka default error message |
| `input.willValidate`      | Kya yeh field validate hoga |

**Key Methods**

| Method                        | Kya Karta Hai? |
|-------------------------------|----------------|
| `checkValidity()`             | Check karta hai, agar invalid to `invalid` event fire |
| `reportValidity()`            | Error message popup/show karta hai |
| `setCustomValidity("message")`| Apna custom error message set karta hai (khali string se clear) |

**Simple Custom Validation Example:**
```js
const password = document.getElementById('password');

password.addEventListener('input', () => {
  if (password.value.length < 8) {
    password.setCustomValidity('Password must be at least 8 characters long.');
  } else {
    password.setCustomValidity('');   // Clear custom message
  }
});
```

### Best Practices & Tips (Article Highlights)

- Pehle HTML5 attributes se shuru karo (kam JS).
- Complex logic ke liye JavaScript Constraint API use karo.
- Error messages **clear, helpful aur short** rakho.
- `:user-invalid` pseudo-class use karo taaki errors sirf tab dikhein jab user kuch type kar chuka ho.
- Accessibility maintain karo (ARIA attributes + proper labels).
- Form submit hone se pehle `form.checkValidity()` check kar sakte ho.
- **Never rely only on client-side** â€” server pe validation + sanitization zaroori hai.
- Custom JS validation se bachao jab tak zaruri na ho (accessibility issues ho sakte hain).

### Browser Support
HTML5 Constraint Validation ka support **bahut achha** hai (almost all modern browsers).  
Lekin purane browsers mein fallback (extra JS) rakhna better hai.

